genresAdvancedInfo.name: german contemporary classical
genresAdvancedInfo.description: German contemporary classical music is a genre of classical music that emerged in Germany in the 20th century. It is characterized by its experimental and avant-garde approach to composition, often incorporating elements of electronic music, jazz, and rock. German contemporary classical composers often use unconventional instruments and techniques to create complex and challenging works that push the boundaries of traditional classical music.
